        <div class="col-sm-8 p-3 text-dark">
            There are approximately 14,000 CrossFit affiliates, known as boxes, and an estimated 5 million
            athletes worldwide. It began in 2000 in California, in the US by Greg and Lauren Glassman. The first Games event was in
            2007. Today CrossFit prides itself on being an inclusive fitness model, as there are 37 different divisions from men’s,
            women’s and a multitude of adaptive divisions so no one will ever be excluded from participating in any CrossFit
            competition
