    <h2 class="pageheaders"> What it's all about</h2>
    <div class="row p-3">        
        <div class="col-sm-8 p-3 text-dark">
            The year begins with the Open where over 400,000 athletes of differing abilities compete in their own boxes or at home
            for a chance to qualify for the CrossFit Quarterfinals, where the top 10% from the open can qualify. From there the top
            individual athletes and the top teams can advance to the CrossFit Semi-finals. There are 14 Semi Final events and the
            top 5 in each division from each event progresses to the CrossFit Games. Unfortunately, due to covid these events and
            number of participating athletes is constantly changing.
            <br /><br />
            With approximately 99 affiliates on the island of Ireland with 36 in the north and 63 in the south CrossFit is well
            known in Ireland. One of the most prominent Irish CrossFit athletes is Emma McQuaid, she first competed in 2014 in the
            open where she finished 6,480. She has since gone from strength to strength and finished 1st in the 2021 Semi Finals and
            12th in the CrossFit Games.
        </div>
